      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrates <2% change in all three QoIs between medium and fine mesh densities.",
      "rationale": "Three mesh densities (coarse 1.5 mm, medium 0.8 mm, fine 0.4 mm global element size) were evaluated. QoI variation between medium and fine meshes was 0.9% for stiffness, 1.4% for yield force, and 1.1% for force at 40 mm. Medium mesh adopted for production runs. Richardson extrapolation GCI < 1.5%. Required level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver residuals converge to <1e-6 for all load steps; energy balance error <0.1%.",
      "rationale": "Newton-Raphson convergence achieved within 8 iterations per load step. Force residual norm < 1e-7; displacement residual < 1e-8. Energy balance error 0.04%. Required level 2 achieved."
